  "prompt": "What is the orignal full form of RPG in Russian?",
  "response": "In Russian, the acronym **RPG** originally stands for **\"\u0420\u0443\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043c\u0451\u0442\"** (*Ruchnoy Protivotankovyy Granatomyot*). This translates to **\"Handheld Anti-Tank Grenade Launcher\"** in English.\n\n### Breakdown of the Term:\n- **\u0420\u0443\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0439 (Ruchnoy):** Handheld\n- **\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 (Protivotankovyy):** Anti-tank\n- **\u0413\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043c\u0451\u0442 (Granatomyot):** Grenade launcher\n\n### Context:\nThe RPG series, particularly the **RPG-7**, is one of the most widely recognized and used anti-tank weapons globally. Developed in the Soviet Union, the RPG-7 has been employed by numerous countries and non-state actors due to its portability, effectiveness, and ease of use.\n\n### Additional Meaning:\nIt's worth noting that **RPG** can also refer to **\"\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\"** (*rolevaya igra*) in Russian, which means **\"Role-Playing Game\"** in English. This usage is analogous to the English acronym RPG used in the context of gaming.\n\nHowever, when referring to the original and traditional meaning in Russian, especially in a military context, **\"\u0420\u0443\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043c\u0451\u0442\"** is the primary expansion of the acronym RPG.",
